{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S2 70c7: Content-addressed snapshot cache — cache read/populate path)]\n\nVERDICT: EMPTY G3 findings list. The union of the WHOLE eight-story roster (S1 6d56 materialize core, S2 70c7 THIS cache read/populate, S2b b73c janitor/reclamation, S3 fa49 gate threading, S4 30b3 attested signing, S4b e308 claim-gate coherence/ADR 0002, S5 b7fa CLI/MCP surfaces, S6 1ba5 docs) covers every parent acceptance/success criterion; no uncovered parent criterion is attributable to this pairing.\n\nGROUNDING: this child's CURRENT body has exactly six ACs, all on the cache READ/POPULATE path (in-process single-flight; cross-process flock(LOCK_EX) single-flight; delete-on-last-close reader safety; ENOENT/read-error self-heal; touch-on-read mtime LRU signal; populate-side byte-total increment). Materialization is delegated to S1 (What: \"populated via S1's atomic dir-rename\"; Scope: \"Out: materialization itself (S1)\"). The janitor/reclamation/eviction/disk-reclamation/tunables/ADR are explicitly scoped OUT to sibling S2b dodgy-luff-quasar (b73c), which IS present in the roster and owns them (b73c AC1-AC10, confirmed). The title still reads \"+ background janitor\" — a residual stale LABEL = a G4 staleness note, NOT a G3 coverage gap, since S2b owns that work.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> roster owner; THIS child's bucket):\n- AC1 (no attested gate reads the working tree; all read a faithful snapshot at the pinned SHA) — FULLY by S1 (materialize) + S3 (gate re-root). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (it caches, doesn't materialize). Not an absence.\n- AC2 (signed verdict binds verified_at_sha via the manifest channel; reproducible; no payload-schema/version change; prior signatures verify) — FULLY by S4 atop S1's immutable-SHA basis. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (reinforces reproducibility via the no-staleness content-addressed key; does not sign). Not an absence.\n- AC3 (local reads in-place AND cannot sign; documented back-out) — by S3 (in-place; \"no materialization, no cache\") + S4 (signing bar) + S6 (docs). STRUCTURAL (local bypasses this cache). Not an absence.\n- AC4 (concurrent gates on same/different SHAs without git-lock contention or cross-op corruption; cache + JANITOR reclaim disk under a defined free-space watermark WITHOUT disrupting in-flight reads) — FULLY, SPLIT cleanly: THIS child is PRIMARY OWNER of the single-flight + reader-safety half (AC1 same-SHA single-flight; AC2 cross-process flock single-flight; AC3 delete-on-last-close so eviction-under-fd is harmless + clean miss/re-materialize; AC4 ENOENT/read-error self-heal; AC5 no PID/heartbeat lease). The reclaim sub-clause is S2b (b73c AC1/AC6 — rename-to-trash-not-in-place-rmtree RIDING this child's delete-on-last-close AC3). Atomic-population + no-worktree + no-index.lock/config.lock half is S1. No double-implementation; no gap.\n- AC5 (private-repo fetch failure -> actionable credential error) — FULLY by S1 (raises) + S6 (documents). STRUCTURAL (fetch is S1's step). Not an absence.\n- AC6 (portable: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — FULLY by S1 (pure-Python extraction, gettempdir/mkdtemp, fcntl.flock + atomic-mkdir fallback) + S6 (docs). This child's flock(LOCK_EX) on locks/<sha> RIDES that seam without re-owning the tar/tmp/fallback sub-clauses. STRUCTURAL. Not an absence.\n- AC7 (operational tunables: free-space watermark, default ref, grace/age windows configurable with documented defaults (S2/S3)) — watermark + grace/age owned by S2b (b73c AC9, confirmed); default ref by S3/S5; docs by S6. This child's CURRENT body carries no tunables AC (they live with the janitor on S2b). Covered by the roster; NOT an absence at this child.\n- AC8 (ADR captures architecture + rejected alternatives: PID-lease, payload-schema SHA binding) — cache/janitor architecture + rejected PID+heartbeat-lease ADR owned by S2b (b73c AC10, confirmed); payload-schema SHA-binding rejected alternative by S4 (30b3); ADR 0002 by S4b (e308). This child carries no ADR AC and need not. Covered-by-named-consumer; NOT an absence.\n- final AC (all EIGHT children closed; make lint + full suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion; covered by the existence of all eight children (this is S2 of 8) + each child's green-bar obligation. Not an absence at this child.\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative decomposes onto AC1-AC8: the \"SAFELY UNDER CONCURRENT DISTRIBUTED USE\" clause splits across THIS child's single-flight + delete-on-last-close reader safety (read path) and S2b's reclaim-without-corrupting-readers (janitor); the immutable-SHA content-addressed key (no staleness) is what makes \"reproducible snapshot\" hold across cache hits; signed/reproducible/verified_at_sha -> S4; unsigned-local verify-before-push -> S3. No uncovered obligation introduced.\n\nNamed-consumer/delegation cross-checks (covered-by-named-consumer, not absences): materialization -> S1 (named in What+Scope); janitor/reclamation/tunables/ADR -> S2b b73c (named in this child's Why+Scope: \"RECLAMATION ... is the sibling janitor story\"; \"Out: eviction / janitor / disk reclamation (sibling janitor story)\"); signing -> S4; verdict memoization -> deferred fast-follow (parent Out-of-scope). Each delegated obligation is claimed by a named sibling present in the roster or is out of epic scope.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the cache READ/POPULATE slice (content-addressed SHA-keyed layout, in-process + cross-process single-flight, delete-on-last-close reader safety, touch-on-read mtime LRU signal, populate-side byte-total, read-error self-heal) — co-owner of the concurrency/reader-safety half of parent AC4 and supplier of the read-side primitives (mtime LRU signal, byte-total, delete-on-last-close) S2b's janitor consumes for AC4's reclaim clause. Every parent acceptance/success criterion has a named owner in the eight-story roster; none is left uncovered. NO G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782534741966723001,"uuid":"dc88699f-7d5e-4a11-8300-b44b0b351246"}